Enjoyed the opportunity to chat on CNN with John King about BG’s release. Here are some additional facts:
- BG’s detention was politically motivated, hence the excessive length of her sentence for the crime she was charged with.
- President Biden successfully negotiated the return of former US Marine Trevor Reed a few short months ago. 
- US officials pushed for a Griner AND Paul Whelan return together but Russian officials said no. His espionage case was treated differently. It was BG or nothing. (Note that Whelan has been detained in Russia since 2018, two years before Biden became president.)
- WNBA players have and will likely continue to play overseas in the off-season to supplement their income. While salaries, compensation, and marketing opportunities are increasing domestically, for many players overseas contracts are simply too lucrative to turn down.

From the first time I picked up as basketball, I always wanted to find a hoop. My dad would drive me to the local elementary school’s outdoor courts and rebound for me for hours. Eventually we got a hoop in front of our house. And my passion for the game grew stronger. I could play out there all day. I wanted to get better and honestly, I just loved how the game made me feel.  My ‘why’ is for this little girl. The one who my parents supported to play a sport they knew nothing about - all they knew was that it made me work hard and made me happy. #RememberTheWhy @adidasbasketball #createdwithadidas

Spent the last couple days as a reminder to always be kind to myself. The competitor in me was so sad and frustrated for losing two consecutive Euroleague finals, when in reality this moment was so much bigger than that.

This one hurts because I love this group and our story so much. There’s so much beauty in sports, even in defeat. The transformation and growth of this team in the last 3 months has been nothing short of remarkable. I’m so thankful to Roberto for coming in and believing in us from day one. And for my amazing teammates doing the same. Representing @cukurovabasketbol and Mersin in an all-Turkish Euroleague Final was really remarkable. Given all this country and its people have been through over the last few months… I’m truly so proud. This team is so special to me and there is still plenty to play for in this last stretch of our season. We’ll be back. 🧡💙
